Bye Bye Joe Hockey goodbye The former Treasurer has resigned. Denis Carnahan and Rocco Fazzari reflect on budgets past. With apologies to Don McLean (and Madonna).
PT1M7S 620 349 It's the true end of an era.
Smoking Joe bids us farewell, there are stories of broken tables and bones as rumours of a bare chested dancing Tony Abbott come to light, while Penny Wong turns detective hot on the trail of littered pieces of shattered Italian marble.
Will we ever see the likes of such events and characters now that messiah Malcolm has risen to save us?
While we prepare to enter a new era, we salute a passing one as resident musician Denis Carnahan matches words and music to animation with full apologies to Don McLean and Madonna.
